I had broken teeth due to which food was directly pressing gums and was very painful. I went to another dentist earlier. He did the filling and suggested that if the filling is broken we need to go for the cap. Then I wanted to go to more experienced doctor as I dont want to go for cap yet. I found Dr Seetharam through Practo. Dr Seetharaman had suggested not to go for cap yet but to go for filling leaving slight GAP between the broken teeth and the adjacent one, and see if works. Filling is done with GAP but within 3 months the filling is broken. I met Mr. Seetharam again after 3 months but this time another doctor (Tejaswi) has done the filling without GAP. Dr. Seetharam suggested that the filling lasts 1 yr max (in my case its just 3 months). We usually try filling twice and then will go for rootcanal + cap after that.
